## Core Repo Files

- `AGENTS.md`: base governance contract
- `arch.md`: current architecture and major design decisions
- `plan.md`: prioritized roadmap and approved direction
- `build.sh`: convenience wrapper for Unix, Linux, and Git-Bash environments
- `cmd/build/main.go`: Go build helper, included only for Go-based repos
- `docs/development-cycle.md`: workflow from roadmap through release
- `docs/ac-template.md`: acceptance-criteria template for new work
- `docs/build-release.md`: build, test, and release rules
- `cmd/rel/main.go`: Go release helper, included only for Go-based repos

## Working Agreement

- use `AGENTS.md` as the repo governance contract
- keep `arch.md` current when the architecture materially changes
- keep `plan.md` current when priorities or approved work change
- use `docs/` for acceptance criteria, critiques, and supporting reference material

## Workflow Summary

1. clarify the next approved work item in `plan.md`
2. draft an acceptance-criteria doc from `docs/ac-template.md`
3. implement with tests and direct doc updates
4. run the build and test workflow in `docs/build-release.md`
5. trigger release work only when explicitly requested

